# Project Structure

This rule outlines the structure of the Alt Regioni project to help AI tools navigate and understand the codebase organization.

## Directory Structure Overview

- `/src`: Main source code directory
  - `/client`: Frontend Nuxt.js application
  - `/server`: Backend API endpoints and services
  - `/content`: Content files (markdown, etc.)
  - `/image`: Image processing functionality
  - `/lib`: Shared libraries and utilities
  - `/languages`: Internationalization files
  - `/public`: Static public assets

## Client Structure

The client-side application uses Nuxt.js with Vue 3 and TypeScript:

- `/src/client/app`: Main application component
- `/src/client/assets`: Static assets (CSS, images)
- `/src/client/components`: Vue components
  - `/ui`: Shadcn UI components
  - `/organizations`: Organization-related components
  - `/users`: User-related components
  - `/forms`: Form-related components
  - `/DataTable`: Data table components
- `/src/client/layouts`: Layout components (admin, default)
- `/src/client/pages`: Page components
  - `/auth`: Authentication pages
  - `/organizations`: Organization pages
  - `/users`: User pages
- `/src/client/plugins`: Nuxt plugins
- `/src/client/lib`: Client-side utilities
- `/src/client/api`: API client code
  - `/better`: Improved API client modules
  - `/generated`: Auto-generated API clients
  - `/mutator`: API mutation utilities

## Server Structure

The server-side code follows a REST API structure:

- `/src/server/api`: API endpoint handlers
  - `/auth`: Authentication endpoints
  - `/comments`: Comment management endpoints
  - `/files`: File management endpoints
  - `/folders`: Folder management endpoints
  - `/forms`: Form management endpoints
  - `/form-templates`: Form template endpoints
  - `/form-fields`: Form field endpoints
  - `/review-flows`: Review flow endpoints
  - `/file-shares`: File sharing endpoints
- `/src/server/errors`: Centralized error handling

## Shared Libraries

- `/src/lib`: Shared utilities used by both client and server
  - `/auth.ts`: Authentication utilities server client Prisma
  - `/auth-client.ts`: Client-side authentication utilities
  - `/permissions.ts`: Permission management system
  - `/prisma.ts`: Prisma ORM client setup
  - `/utils.ts`: General utility functions

## Database

- `/prisma`: Prisma ORM configuration
  - `/schema.prisma`: Database schema definition
  - `/migrations`: Database migrations

## Configuration Files

- `nuxt.config.ts`: Nuxt.js configuration
- `tailwind.config.js`: Tailwind CSS configuration
- `tsconfig.json`: TypeScript configuration
- `i18n.config.ts`: Internationalization configuration
- `eslint.config.mjs`: ESLint configuration
- `components.json`: Component configuration (shadcn)
- `orval.config.ts`: Orval API client generation configuration
- `openapi.yaml`: OpenAPI specification

## Development Practices

1. The project uses Vue 3 Composition API with `<script setup lang="ts">` syntax
2. Component files use PascalCase (.vue files)
3. Utility files use kebab-case
4. The project follows shadcn-vue component patterns
5. Typescript strict mode is enabled
6. Error handling is centralized in server/errors
